About
Quranic Park is a pioneering modern, cultural project that emerges from the cultural and scientific achievements of Islam, a wonderful opportunity to explain many wonderful meanings and miracles that the Holy Quran contains in the scientific and medical fields. The Park is open daily, kindly check the operational hours before taking the trip as it changes frequently on National and Public Holidays. Jogging area is open 24 hours. Park entrance is free of charge, however there is fee for two attractions: ticket price is AED 10 for entrance to the Cave of the Miracles (AED 5) and Glass House (AED 5) located inside the Quranic Park. Kids below three years of age, people of determination enter for free. Customers can use RTA NOL card, also recharge it inside the Park. Public transportation to Quranic Park E66, X23, X123 as well as public taxis are available right the entrance gate of Quranic Park.
Duration: 1-2 hours

    Most Amazing experience
    It was one of the best places we have visited as a Muslim family in Dubai. The miracle cave videos were very educational and the guide asked us multiple questions throughout that made the experience even more exciting for our four children. We then proceeded to the glass house and what an experience that was. Our guide Abdul Kareem was excellent. He gave us a guided tour of all the plants, asked us multiple questions, told us the characteristics of each plant or fruit and made us reflect on those characteristics and how it relates to us in our day to day lives. Abdul Kareem also made us reflect on our own Quranic knowledge and ayahs in the Quran that we related to most. It’s definitely worth a visit for Muslims and non Muslims alike and us as a family of 6 with4 children aged between 7-12 years thoroughly enjoyed it. We ended up spending over 3 hours here when originally thinking we would be done in one. Absolutely loved it and if you get to have a tour of the glass house with Abdul Kareem go for it!!
